    "description": "Bratislava, Slovakia's capital, is a charming city where medieval history meets modern development. Perched on the banks of the Danube River, it's the only capital city that borders two countries (Austria and Hungary). The city's compact Old Town features colorful Baroque buildings, while the imposing Bratislava Castle overlooks the city from its hilltop position. Known as the 'Coronation City', it was the site of Hungarian royal coronations for nearly 300 years. The unique UFO Bridge and modern Eurovea development showcase the city's contemporary side, while nearby Devin Castle ruins offer a glimpse into its ancient past. Bratislava's small size and walkable streets make it an ideal destination for exploring Central European history and culture.",
